Obviously not. The creature let out a roar and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Thank goodness, although Sasalin was large in size, it was still agile enough to dodge in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream, nearly slipping off Sasalin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"This is too difficult!"
Sasalin let out a roar, circled around, and flew toward the mountain it called home. The black monster followed closely, but when it was attacked by flames from behind, it seemed somewhat panicked. This creature had not yet realized it now had another opponent. Sasalin slowed down and then struck the monster's head with its tail, knocking it off course, and the monster became even more panicked.
The monster roared, emitting a hissing sound from its throat, flying straight upward while continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, the surroundings turned pitch black, as if the monster were siphoning the light from the sky and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasalin's vision went black, and he tried to step back, but found himself colliding with the branches, then falling onto the open ground. The monster seemed clearly aware of where Sasalin had fallen, flying straight toward him and carrying the dark cloud with it.
"Kayer!" Tenuk shouted as he flew out of the dark cloud, beginning to circle in an attempt to locate Nisi and Sasalin in the darkness below. "What should we do? Kayer...? Kayer, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to stand up. She felt certain she had broken some bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability had already begun to take effect. Sasalin's situation was different; he lay helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked over. Nisi made an effort to walk toward Sasalin, but her vision was completely dark, and she could hardly see anything. Everywhere was filled with terrifying shadows, and something was screaming within them.
A terrifying club-like tail smashed down onto the ground, flipping Nisi over. She noticed the tail was swinging wildly, but its target seemed not to be her. Nisi barely managed to see that the monster was roaring, clawing at the shadows it had created with its claws. Something was teleporting within the darkness, waiting for an opportunity to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot cracked through the air, and the monster immediately went silent, falling to the ground motionless. The surrounding darkness dispersed, revealing the truth of the situation. Kayer stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding the rifle, breathing heavily.
"that was... one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tantos Caterolon..." Kayer gasped, his breath coming in heavy bursts. Somehow, his eyes were glowing with black light, and a surge of dark energy was flowing through his body. But just as Kayer began to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes reverted back to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nisi finally realized what had happened. They all knew that Kayer possessed eerie shadow abilities, but he rarely used them because most people considered this power extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nisi didn't know that Kayer could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kayer's reaction, it seemed that he was just as surprised as she was.
"Are you okay?" Nisi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon." Kayer looked at his "masterpiece," and at that moment, Tenuk landed beside him, reverting back to his original Spartus form.
Now that the monster no longer moved, they could finally take a good look at what it really was. Its skin was dark and shiny, covered with a sticky layer of liquid that clung tightly to its body. It had four wings and four legs, each ending in long claws, and two straight horns grew from its skull.
Tenuk and Kayer hadn't had time to ask what kind of thing this was when a monster suddenly screamed and burst out from the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car crashed into the monster's side, causing it to skid for a distance before coming to a stop by Nisi's feet. Nisi didn't hesitate and grabbed the shotguns, firing a shot at the monster's head, which instantly killed it.
“Ow...” Retwick grumbled as he sat in the driver’s seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed down from the truck. “Uh, I didn’t mean to. Are you two okay?”
“you missed all the fun!” Tenuk snorted. “Where did you go?”
“it was you two who left me behind. I’ve done my best to catch up…” Retwick sighed. “Excuse me, what are these terrifying things?”
Retwick's question was answered by Sasalin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looking a bit dazed, but his injuries seemed not to be serious.
"You killed the Corrupted! Those infected monsters. When the Corruption attacked your god, these creatures were left behind here."
"Are you saying... we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Tenuk stammered.
"Yes, that's true. There might be more Corrupted. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And fighting two to one isn't fair, right?" Sasalin walked up to Kayer and patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You reminded me of my old friend Alcardin. Only you aren't as cruel as him, and you don't have his destructive power to destroy the universe."
"Er... thank you... I think..." Kayer shrugged. "So, er, did we complete the mission?"
Nisi shrugged, picked up the camera, and took a few photos of the monsters that had clearly died. Then she pulled out her favorite dagger—the exquisite Death's Dagger—and began cutting off one of the monster's horns, followed by another. However, the moment Nisi finished the cutting, the monsters suddenly burst into flames and quickly turned into piles of ash. The horns she had cut off also turned to ash.
"Okay... this is definitely a double-edged sword..." Nisi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
